# Jongara Game Rules and Mechanics

This document defines the core game rules and mechanics that must be implemented:

## Game Mechanics
1. **Tile Selection**: Players can only select tiles that are not blocked by other tiles
2. **Hand Management**: The hand can hold a maximum of 7 tiles
3. **Matching**: When 3 identical tiles are in the hand, they are automatically removed
4. **Victory**: Player wins when all tiles are cleared from the board
5. **Defeat**: Player loses when the hand is full (7 tiles) and no matches can be made

## Power-ups
1. **Undo**: Allows reverting the last move (limited to 1 use per level)
2. **Shuffle**: Randomizes all currently selectable tiles (limited to 1 use per level)

## Level Design
- **Chapter 1 (Levels 1-3)**: Simple layouts with few tile types (wan and tong suits only)
- **Chapter 2 (Levels 4-7)**: Medium complexity with more tile types (adds tiao and some honor tiles)
- **Chapter 3 (Levels 8-12)**: Complex layouts with all tile types and challenging arrangements

## Tile Types
- **Wan (萬)**: Character tiles numbered 1-9
- **Tong/Bing (筒)**: Circle/dot tiles numbered 1-9
- **Tiao/Suo (条)**: Bamboo tiles numbered 1-9
- **Honor Tiles**: Wind tiles (East, South, West, North) and Dragon tiles (Red, Green, White)

## Game Logic Requirements
- Always generate solvable board layouts
- Implement proper overlap detection for tile selection
- Track and update selectable tiles after each move
- Validate matches in the hand after each move
- Check win/loss conditions after each move